block.comment: These are some simple tests addressing the integration of the snap2js compiler into a netsblox service.

custom-block.l: be able to send messages from the server

block.l: try { var process = arguments[2]; console.log(arguments[2]) process.handleError = function(error, block) { error.message = 'Failing test "it should ' + name + '": ' + error.message; Process.prototype.handleError.call(this, error, block); }; process.doRun(action, new List()); //action.apply(this, [process]); //process.evaluate(action, new List(), true); } catch (e) { console.log('caught', e); throw new Error(name + ' failed: ' + e); }
